<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Hosea 1:1-11</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="14">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="11">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">The word of Jehovah that occurred to Ho&middot;se&acute;a the son of Be&middot;e&acute;ri in the days of Uz&middot;zi&acute;ah, Jo&acute;tham, A&acute;haz [and] Hez&middot;e&middot;ki&acute;ah, kings of Judah, and in the days of Jer&middot;o&middot;bo&acute;am the son of Jo&acute;ash, the king of Israel.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">There was a start of the word of Jehovah by Ho&middot;se&acute;a, and Jehovah proceeded to say to Ho&middot;se&acute;a: “Go, take to yourself a wife of fornication and children of fornication, because by fornication the land positively turns from following Jehovah.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">And he proceeded to go and take Go&acute;mer the daughter of Dib&middot;la&acute;im, so that she became pregnant and in time bore to him a son.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">And Jehovah went on to say to him: “Call his name Jez&acute;re&middot;el, for yet a little while and I must hold an accounting for the acts of bloodshed of Jez&acute;re&middot;el against the house of Je&acute;hu, and I must cause the royal rule of the house of Israel to cease.</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">And it must occur in that day that I must break the bow of Israel in the low plain of Jez&acute;re&middot;el.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">And she proceeded to become pregnant another time and to give birth to a daughter. And He went on to say to him: “Call her name Lo-ru&middot;ha&acute;mah, for I shall no more show mercy again to the house of Israel, because I shall positively take them away.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">But to the house of Judah I shall show mercy, and I will save them by Jehovah their God; but I shall not save them by a bow or by a sword or by war, by horses or by horsemen.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">And she gradually weaned Lo-ru&middot;ha&acute;mah, and she proceeded to become pregnant and give birth to a son.</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">So He said: “Call his name Lo-am&acute;mi, because <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> men are not my people and I myself shall prove to be not <span class="smallcaps">YOURS</span>.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">“And the number of the sons of Israel must become like the grains of the sand of the sea that cannot be measured or numbered. And it must occur that in the place in which it used to be said to them, ‘Y<span class="smallcaps">OU</span> men are not my people,’ it will be said to them, ‘The sons of the living God.’</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">And the sons of Judah and the sons of Israel will certainly be collected together into a unity and will actually set up for themselves one head and go up out of the land, because great will be the day of Jez&acute;re&middot;el.</span>
</p>
</form>

