<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Hosea 3:1-5</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="14">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="5">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">And Jehovah went on to say to me: “Go once again, love a woman loved by a companion and committing adultery, as in the case of Jehovah’s love for the sons of Israel while they are turning to other gods and are loving raisin cakes.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">And I proceeded to purchase her for myself for fifteen silver [pieces] and a ho&acute;mer measure of barley and a half-ho&acute;mer of barley.</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">Then I said to her: “For many days you will dwell as mine. You must not commit fornication, and you must not come to belong to [another] man; and I also will be for you.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">It is because for many days the sons of Israel will dwell without a king and without a prince and without a sacrifice and without a pillar and without an eph&acute;od and teraphim.</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">Afterwards the sons of Israel will come back and certainly look for Jehovah their God, and for David their king; and they will certainly come quivering to Jehovah and to his goodness in the final part of the days.</span>
</p>
</form>

